Spiced Cranberry Holiday Punch (serves 8)

• 2 cups of green tea (or any tea of choice)
• 1 cup of fresh orange juice
• 1/2 cup of fresh lime juice
• 1 cup of spiced cranberry syrup (recipe below)
• Sparkling water (or ginger ale)

Instructions: Combine all ingredients into a pitcher, or punch bowl, and lightly stir to combine. Serve & pour into a rocks glass over ice, and garnish with a fresh orange & lime wheel.

Spiced Cranberry Syrup:
In a medium saucepan, combine 2 cups of water, 2-3 cups of fresh cranberries, 1 cup of freshly pared orange peels, 3-4 broken up cinnamon sticks. Bring to a light simmer, then add in 2 cups of sugar and lightly stir to dissolve the sugar. Remove the syrup from the heat and allow to cool down. Strain the syrup to remove the solids, then store the syrup in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

Note: To make this boozy, substitute the tea for any spirit of choice. Aged rum or bourbon is recommended.

@stranahans Blue Peak is one of my favorite Stranahan’s American Single Malt expressions to sip on with friends, especially during the holidays. It’s great as a neat pour, or mixed up in spirit forward cocktails perfect for these chilly Colorado days ❄️ This Brown Sugar Old Fashioned features Blue Peak, banana liqueur, brown sugar syrup, chocolate bitters and it is so good! The best part is it’s easily batched in larger amounts so all you need to do is batch, pour & sip. The recipe breakdown for a single serve & batched version is below. Cheers! #Stranahans #Ad #For21+
-
Ingredients:
• 2 oz Stranahan’s Blue Peak
• 1/4 oz Banana Liqueur
• 1/4 oz Brown sugar syrup
• 2 dashes chocolate bitters (or aromatic bitters)

Method:
Combine ingredients into a mixing glass, and stir with ice. Strain the drink into a rocks glass over ice, and garnish with fresh grated chocolate (or nutmeg) and a dried banana chip.
-
Batched Version (Makes 10 old fashioneds)
• 2.5 Cups of Stranahan’s Blue Peak
• 2.5 ounces of Banana liqueur
• 2.5 ounces of Brown sugar syrup
• 8-10 dashes of chocolate bitters
• 2.5 ounces of water (for dilution)

Combine all ingredients into glass bottle or pitcher & lightly stir. Pour, sip & enjoy! Cheers!

Here’s my go to holiday old fashioned with @oldforester. #ad Vanilla Demerara syrup, chocolate bitters, and Old Forester 86, which pairs so perfectly with the other ingredients due to its rich, full flavor & vanilla flavor profile 🥃 Check out the recipe breakdown below to make this cocktail for your upcoming holiday. Cheers! #OldForesterPartner #For21+
-
Ingredients
• 2 oz Old Forester 86 Proof
• 1/4 oz Vanilla Demerara Syrup
• 2-3 dashes Chocolate bitters

Method
Combine all ingredients into a mixing glass and stir with ice. Strain the drink into a rocks glass over ice, and garnish with fresh grated nutmeg & an orange peel.

How to Make Vanilla Demerara Syrup
In a medium saucepan, combine 1 cup of water, 1.5 cup of Demerara sugar, and 1 vanilla bean pod split lengthwise with the seeds scraped out and added to the mix. Bring to a light simmer, and lightly stir to dissolve the sugar. Remove the syrup from the heat, and allow it to cool down. Strain out the vanilla bean solids and store the syrup in a glass jar in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

Method:
Combine ingredients into a glass mug, and garnish with a toasted marshmallow.

“A great drink doesn’t have to include alcohol,” says mixologist Elliott Clark. “It’s all about the experience.” (As the creative force behind @apartment_bartender, he’s an expert on elevated at-home sipping.) Here's his go-to recipe for Dry January:

Sparkling Honey Grapefruit Mocktail

🥃 Combine 2 oz. green tea, 1 oz. grapefruit juice, 1/2 oz. lime juice, and 3/4 oz. honey syrup in a cocktail shaker, and shake with ice.

🥃 Strain into a glass filled with ice, and add a splash of sparkling water.
 
🥃 Garnish with a sprig of rosemary and grapefruit wedge.

Teaming up with my friends at @lobos1707 to help you prep for the big game 🏈🍹 This Lobos Big Game Punch Bowl is the perfect (and simple) recipe to mix up to celebrate the day with your pack. Lobos Joven, orange liqueur, fresh citrus, and more - all you to do is batch, pour, sip & enjoy! The full recipe is below. Cheers! #LobosPartner #AllForthePack #BuildABiggerTable

Lobos Big Game Punch Bowl
(Serves 8-12 People)

Ingredients:
• (1) 750ml bottle of Lobos Joven
• 1.5 cups Fresh Orange Juice
• 6 ounces Orange Liqueur
• 6 ounces Fresh Lime Juice
• 3 ounces of Agave nectar

Method:
Combine all ingredients to a punch bowl. Add ice, and lightly stir to chill & dilute the punch bowl. Add fresh citrus wheels for garnish. Serve & enjoy!

A fresh Blackberry Gimlet for ya! It’s a simple & great recipe to keep up your sleeve for Valentine’s Day (and any day) ✨ Recipe specs below - Cheers! #ValentinesDay #ApartmentBartender
-
Ingredients
• 2 oz Gin (I used @barrhillgin) 
• 1 oz Fresh Lime Juice
• .5 oz Agave nectar (or 3/4 oz simple syrup)
• 3-4 Blackberries

Method:
Combine the ingredients into a cocktail shaker and muddle the blackberries. Add ice, and shake. Strain the drink into a cocktail glass, and garnish with a speared blackberry.

-
Spicy Cucumber Margaritas
Serves (2)

Ingredients:
• 4 oz Tequila (I used @herradurateq Reposado)
• 2 oz fresh lime juice
• 1.5 orange liqueur (I used @cointreau_us)
• 1/2 oz agave nectar
• 4-5 cucumber slices
• 4 jalapeño slices

Method:
Combine all ingredients into a cocktail shaker, and muddle the cucumber and jalapeños slices. Add ice & shake, then strain the drink into a rocks glass over ice. Garnish with a lime wheel and cucumber slice.

Back with another Apartment Bartending 101 ✨ This time giving a little perspective on the (3) most common types of cocktail shakers I see best for home use. Let me know if this is helpful, and be sure to drop any questions + comments below! #ApartmentBartender
-
1. Cobbler Shakers: a three piece shaker with a built in strainer.

2. Shaker tins (or Boston shakers)

3. Parisian Shakers: similar to cobbler shakers, minus the built in strainer.
-
Personally, I use the shaker tins and/or the cobbler shakers. Whatever you choose for your home bar, make sure you feel comfortable using it, and that it’s functional. Below are a few great brands for solid barware:

• @cocktailkingdom
• @viskicraft
• @pinabarware
• @elevatedcraft

We’ll be celebrating St. Patricks Day at home with this classic cocktail featuring @teelingwhiskey ☘️ This Irish Coffee is unique as it incorporates a special roast from Variety Coffee Roasters - the coffee’s notes of candied apple, walnut, and dark chocolate combine perfectly with the warm finish and lingering sweetness of Teeling Small Batch. I can’t think of a better way to commemorate the day. The full recipe breakdown to this simple classic is below! How are you celebrating today?

#TEELINGPARTNER #TEELINGSMALLBATCH #IRISHWHISKEY #IRISHCOFFEE #STPATRICKSDAY #THINGSTODOINNYC #AD #FOR21+

INGREDIENTS
• 1.5 parts Teeling Small Batch Irish Whiskey
• 4 parts Variety Coffee Teeling Small Batch Roast
• 1⁄2 part Demerara Syrup
• Bar spoon of Heavy Cream

BUILD
In a warmed glass, mix Teeling Whiskey, brewed coffee, syrup and stir to combine. Top with cream from the back of a bar spoon. Garnish with grated nutmeg.

Partnering with @drycreekvalleywines to highlight the beauty of this region & all the ways you can enjoy Zinfandel wines to elevate your get togethers at home ✨

Dry Creek Valley is a premium wine growing region in Sonoma County where more than 150 winegrowers and 60 wineries produce wines from a wide variety of grapes, including the zinfandel - a red wine grape variety, and one of California’s premier crop.

This dry, jammy, and complex red wine is great to sip on it’s own, and pairs so well with food. You know I’m a cocktail guy, so try using a Red Zinfandel to make a Sangria, float on top of a whiskey sour (to make it a NY Sour), or use what’s left over to make a red wine syrup to drizzle over desserts. Which way would you use Zinfandel at your next get together?!

📕 I’M WRITING A BOOK! 📕
-
For the past 7 months I’ve been writing, building drink recipes, and producing the visual content of the book. As stoked as I am about the story & the cocktail recipes, the photos are even more amazing, and I wouldn’t have been able to do that without my brother and studio partner @shawnxcampbell (who told me last year his dream was to shoot a cocktail book).
-
Still a bit to go on the book, we’re currently working through edits, but the heavy lifting is done and I couldn’t be more excited to see this all coming together. The book doesn’t come out until early next year, but I felt it was as good a time as any to share the news. (Also, why I thought I could open a creative studio and write a book at the same time I have no idea, but here we are 😵‍💫😅)
-
To those that have have been on this journey with me since the start, thank you for all your positivity and support along the way—it meant the world 🙏🏽 After 8 years of doing Apartment Bartender I’m finally etching my name on the walls of the drink industry. It’s going to be a special thing walking through the book store with Elijah, seeing him pick this book off the shelf and say “Dada!” ❤️ Author has a nice ring to it ✨ #ApartmentBartender

Setting the holiday mood with @stanley_brand ✨ Home is always what you make it, and for me it’s all about good company, quality conversation, and great drinks. Here I’m mixing up one of my favorite holiday cocktails to make for friends and family with whiskey, fresh coffee, vanilla, brown sugar, and fresh whipped cream, served in Stanley’s Winterscape Stay-Hot Camp Mug. Get the full recipe below - cheers! #Ad
-
Winterscape Holiday Coffee
Ingredients
• 6-8 oz Hot coffee
• 1.5 oz Whiskey (or aged rum)
• 1 oz Vanilla brown sugar syrup
• Top with fresh whipped heavy cream
-
How to Make Vanilla Brown Sugar Syrup
In a medium saucepan, combine 1 cup of water, 1.5 cup of brown sugar, and 1 tablespoon of vanilla extract. Turn the heat to medium, and lightly stir until the sugar is dissolved. Once the sugar is dissolved, turn off the stove and allow the syrup to cool. (Store in a glass jar in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks)

Life is made up of moments, and I’m excited to be creating something special with @Veroni_USA. As busy as the holidays can be, it’s important to set that time aside for you and your special someone to unwind & connect. What better way to do it than over Veroni’s authentic Italian charcuterie and some great drinks?! The cocktail has flavors that pair so well with the charcuterie: rosemary, vanilla, cherry, apple, and more! The recipe is below. Cheers! #VeroniPartner #Charcuterie #Ad
-
• 2 oz Gin
• 1 oz tart cherry juice
• .5 oz lemon juice
• 1/2 oz rosemary vanilla syrup
• Top with Sparkling apple cider
-
Combine the first four ingredients into a cocktail shaker with ice, and shake to chill the drink. Strain into a coupe glass and top with sparkling apple cider. Garnish with a rosemary sprig (lightly burn the ends to create an aromatic trail of smoke)

When you’re ready to raise a glass at the end of the day, #MakeItMidnight. Enjoying the Midnight expression of @pendletonwhisky finished in American Brandy Barrels - great for sipping neat, on ice, or in my favorite cocktail...an old fashioned. The recipe for this Midnight Old Fashioned is below, cheers! #WithPendleton #PendletonPartner #PendletonMidnight #21andover
-
Midnight Old Fashioned
• 2 oz Pendleton Whisky Midnight
• .25 oz maple syrup
• 2 dashes chocolate bitters

Combine ingredients into a mixing glass, and stir with ice. Strain the drink into a rocks glass over ice, and garnish with an orange peel and cinnamon stick.
